\subsection{Phase 3: Multimodal Analytics and 3D Synthesis}

After the architectural JSON schema is extracted, three parallel execution routes securely synchronize. The Scikit-Learn Predictive Regressor instantly evaluates physical square footage and perimeter mapping to output highly-local expense predictions. Simultaneously, the Groq Advanced LLM interprets incoming room parameters to structure a spatial response logic mapping. Ultimately, the finalized $(x,y)$ blueprint feeds cleanly into the Three.js WebGL canvas—pulling out the Z-axis height array and successfully synthesizing an interactive, responsive 3D representation directly in the native browser.

